ğŸ“Œ Purpose of This Lab

This lab demonstrates how to:

Create IAM groups

Create IAM users

Attach AWS managed policies to a group

Assign users to a group

Validate permission inheritance

It reinforces AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) best practices.

ğŸ§  Core IAM Concepts
IAM Structure
User â†’ Group â†’ Policy â†’ AWS Services

Best Practice:

Do NOT attach policies directly to users

Attach policies to groups

Add users to groups

This ensures scalable and clean permission management.

ğŸ‘¥ IAM Components
1ï¸âƒ£ IAM User

Represents a person or application

Has long-term credentials (username/password or access keys)

2ï¸âƒ£ IAM Group

Collection of users

Used to assign permissions collectively

3ï¸âƒ£ IAM Policy

JSON document defining permissions

Specifies:

Effect (Allow/Deny)

Actions

Resources

4ï¸âƒ£ AWS Managed Policy

Pre-created by AWS

Maintained and updated by AWS

Example:

AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

AmazonEC2ReadOnlyAccess

ğŸ” Permission Model

Permissions are inherited.

Example:

If:

Group = Developers

Policy attached = AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

Users added = user1, user2

Then:
All users in Developers group automatically get S3 read-only access.

ğŸ›  Key Steps Performed in This Lab
1ï¸âƒ£ Create IAM Group

Navigate to IAM â†’ User groups

Click Create group

Provide group name

Attach AWS managed policy

2ï¸âƒ£ Attach AWS Managed Policy

Search for policy

Select appropriate policy

Attach to group

Example policies:

AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

AmazonEC2ReadOnlyAccess

3ï¸âƒ£ Create IAM Users

Navigate to IAM â†’ Users

Click Create user

Enable console access (if required)

Set password

Add user to group

4ï¸âƒ£ Validate Permissions

Open user profile

Go to Permissions tab

Confirm:

Permissions inherited via group

Managed policy attached

ğŸ” Important Commands (CLI Alternative)

Create user:

aws iam create-user --user-name user1

Create group:

aws iam create-group --group-name Developers

Attach policy:

aws iam attach-group-policy \
  --group-name Developers \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

Add user to group:

aws iam add-user-to-group \
  --user-name user1 \
  --group-name Developers
